# Git And PR Discipline

- Keep changes atomic: one coherent purpose per commit/PR.
- Write commit messages that explain why, not only what changed.
- Do not mix unrelated refactors with feature or bug-fix work.
- Run lint/tests relevant to touched areas before finalizing.
- Highlight risk, migration notes, and rollback strategy in PR context.
- Respect branch safety: avoid forceful or destructive history rewrites.
- Call out follow-up work explicitly instead of silently deferring it.
